Love this game - it's a very good reimplementation of a classic that's 
close to my heart. Controls are clean and responsive, but I wish that they 
were able to find a better design than putting the buttons right over the 
character sprites. Difficulty is high - even at the lowest setting, I can 
win maybe three fights, four at most. Finally, the graphics take me back to 
1994, for good and for ill. I also want to highlight that you get the full 
game out the gate. No grinding, no microtransactions here, which matters a 
lot. I can pull it out and have a good time anytime I want, when I want. No 
obligations, no timers, no gatchas. Would buy again.

I've both compliments and complaints about this game:  PRO 1: it brings back memories for just $4, and it's all mine! No more quarter-placing and waiting for the next round.  PRO 2: the game stays true to what the SS-series represents - a whole lot of violence with difficulty that'll keep most novice players away from thinking that it is a "play, beat, then throwaway" kind of a game.  PRO 3: great job on the training section - even on SS1 I wish they had this option so that I could try out the moves for individual characters.    That being said...   CON 1: please decrease the initial difficulty settings, it is WAYYY too difficult! I remember crushing this game on the arcade set around lvl 4 (knew the arcade manager), but even at lvl 1 this Android version is impossible. I'm pretty much stuck at the fifth person and can't go on with the game due to CPU power and intelligence.  CON 2: training mode needs to have a "CPU ATTACK" and "CPU DIFFICULTY" settings so that the player/a can practice in a realistic situation. I always found that helpful when playing KOF games on PSX.  CON 3: can something be done about the controls? There seems to be quite a lag in responsiveness.

content: Works very well on my nexus 4 Love this game and I hope they will bring another king of fighters soon as well.

If you like a game where you aimlessly rub both your thumbs on the screen as if they were nipples, this is the game for you.  In this game the buttons disappear completely from the screen a few seconds after the match begins.  You don't know what you are pressing.  The default button settings are TOO LARGE and the adjusted button settings is TOO SMALL at the very max.  That truly is a tease in the face.  9 Dollars wasted...
